    </sidebyside>
    <p>
      One fact about the number <m>e</m> is that it is the base of the exponential function whose curve has a very unique property.  The function <m>y=e^x</m> is the only function with the property that its tangent line at any given point had a slope equal to the <m>y</m>-coordinate of the point.  In <xref ref=logs-and-exponents-e-and-ln-figure-2>Figure</xref>, the function <m>y=e^x</m> has been drawn along with the tangent lines at the point <m>(0,1</m> as well as the (approximate) point <m>(1.099,3)</m>.  Note that the lines have, respectively, slopes of 1 and 3.
    </p>
